Introduction

01  Mocking is the way to test the functionality of a class in isolation.
02  Mock object do the mock of a real service.
03  Mock objects return dummy data corresponding to some dummy input passed to it.

Mockito

01  Mockito is used to create mock objects.
02  It uses java reflection to create mock objects for a given interface.
03  Mock objects are proxy for actual implementation.

We can also create an object of actual object but we have to initialize all its parameters. Mockito can do it much easily.


